data.chText: 无价的；极珍贵的；极重要的
价值连城的古文物收藏
你真该见识见识他那副尊容——可笑极了！
data.enText: You should have seen his face─it was priceless!

data.chText: 以上各词均用以形容物品值钱、宝贵。
data.enText: These words all describe sth that is worth a lot of money or very important to sb.

data.chText: 窃贼盗走了三件贵重的首饰。
data.enText: The thieves took three pieces of valuable jewellery.

data.chText: 指珍稀的、珍贵的、宝贵的：
data.enText: rare and worth a lot of money; loved or valued very much

data.chText: 价值50万英镑的稀世中国花瓶
data.enText: a precious Chinese vase, valued at half a million pounds

data.chText: 我们共度时光的珍贵回忆
data.enText: precious memories of our time together
[only before noun] loved or valued very much

data.chText: 大火吞噬了我的一些最珍贵的物品。
data.enText: I lost some of my most prized possessions in the fire.

data.chText: 指无价的、极珍贵的、极宝贵的：
data.enText: extremely valuable; loved or valued very much

data.chText: 价值连城的古文物收藏
指因贵重或独特而不能替代的
data.enText: too valuable or special to be replaced

tr: having incalculable monetary, intellectual, or spiritual worth

value.def: If you say that something is priceless, you are emphasizing that it is worth a very large amount of money.

example.ex: They are priceless, unique and irreplaceable.
example.tran: 它们是独一无二、不可替代的无价之宝。

example.ex: ...the priceless treasures of the Royal Collection.
example.tran: 英国王室收藏的无价珍宝

value.tran: 无价的；极贵重的；极为昂贵的

value.def: If you say that something is priceless, you approve of it because it is extremely useful.

example.ex: They are a priceless record of a brief period in British history...
example.tran: 它们是对英国历史上一个短暂时期的极为珍贵的记录。

example.ex: The influence of someone like David York will be priceless.
example.tran: 像大卫·约克这样的人能带来非常积极的影响。

value.boxu_tran: 注意不要混淆 priceless，invaluable 和 worthless。priceless表示非常珍贵，因而难以计算其价值，如：priceless masterpieces by Canova and Bernini（卡诺瓦和贝尔尼尼的无价杰作）。invaluable 表示非常有用，如：It has a spelling checker, which is invaluable if you are dyslexic（它带有一个拼写检查程序，对有诵读困难的人非常有用）。相反，worthless 表示没有什么价值，如：I'm afraid your shares are now worthless（恐怕你的股票现在一文不值了）。
value.boxu_usage: Be careful not to confuse the words priceless, invaluable and worthless. Something which is priceless is so precious that it is difficult to give it a value. …priceless masterpieces by Canova and Bernini. Something which is invaluable is very useful indeed. It has a spelling checker, which is invaluable if you are dyslexic. In contrast, something that is worthless is of very little value. I'm afraid your shares are now worthless.
